# Release Notes - Version 0.0.39

**Release Date:** August 2, 2025  
**Version:** 0.0.39

## 🎉 What's New

### Three-Column Layout System
IslamWiki now features a comprehensive three-column layout system across multiple pages, providing better organization and user experience:

#### Pages Page
- **Left Column (2/10):** Create content section with page statistics
- **Middle Column (6/10):** Hero section and pages list with pagination
- **Right Column (2/10):** Search and filter controls

#### About Page
- **Left Column (2/10):** Get involved section with community actions
- **Middle Column (6/10):** Main content including mission, features, values, and technology
- **Right Column (2/10):** Contact us section with communication methods

#### Dashboard Page
- **Left Column (2/10):** Quick actions and user statistics
- **Middle Column (6/10):** Welcome section, recent activity, and watched pages
- **Right Column (2/10):** Learning resources and site statistics

### Dynamic Site Statistics
The dashboard now displays real-time, accurate site statistics instead of placeholder values:

- **Total Pages:** Real count from the database
- **Active Users:** Actual user count from the users table
- **Total Edits:** Real edit count from page history
- **Categories:** Dynamic count of distinct namespaces

### Enhanced Dashboard Organization
- Consolidated duplicate "Your Contributions" section into "Your Stats"
- Added contribution action buttons directly to the stats card
- Improved space utilization and cleaner layout
- Better responsive design for all screen sizes

## 🔧 Technical Improvements

### Dashboard Controller Enhancements
- Added `getSiteStatistics()` method for dynamic site-wide statistics
- Updated `index()` method to include site statistics in view data
- Improved error handling for database queries

### Template Structure Improvements
- Standardized three-column layout across pages, about, and dashboard
- Enhanced card layouts with better spacing and organization
- Improved responsive design for mobile and desktop
- Better content organization and user flow

## 🐛 Bug Fixes

### Duplicate Information Issues
- Removed redundant "Your Contributions" section from dashboard
- Consolidated user statistics into single "Your Stats" card
- Eliminated duplicate data presentation across dashboard sections

### Static Data Issues
- Replaced hardcoded site statistics with dynamic database queries
- Fixed placeholder values (1,234 users, 5,678 edits, 890 categories)
- Now shows real-time accurate site statistics

## 🔒 Security

- Maintained existing security measures
- No database changes - purely frontend and data presentation improvements
- Backward compatible with all existing functionality

## 📋 System Requirements

- PHP 8.0+
- MySQL 5.7+
- Composer
- Web server (Apache/Nginx)

## 🚀 Installation

1. Update to version 0.0.39
2. Clear browser cache to see new styling
3. No database migrations required

## 📈 Performance

- Improved page load times with better content organization
- Enhanced user experience with logical content flow
- Better mobile responsiveness across all pages

## 🎯 User Experience

- More intuitive navigation with logical content placement
- Better information hierarchy and visual organization
- Improved accessibility with better content structure
- Real-time statistics provide accurate platform insights

